1. **Static Variables**: A static variable is a variable that is shared by all instances of a class. It is initialized only once when the class is loaded into memory, and its value is retained across multiple instances of the class.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static int count = 0;

    public MyClass() {
        count++;
    }
}
```

